The male genitalia (
Fig. 19
) are distinguished by long fingerlike socii, whose lateral margins are nearly parallel. In females, the sterigma (
Figs. 24–26
) is rectangular and elongate (length about 2 times ostium diameter), the posterior margin of sternum 7 is semicircular and diverges laterally from the sterigma, and the ductus bursae has a twist-like sclerotized contortion near the juncture with the ductus seminalis.
